---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const now = new Date();
const months = ['January','February','March','April','May','June','July','August','September','October','November','December'];
const lastUpdated = `${months[now.getMonth()]} ${now.getFullYear()}`;
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — RingAdvice" description="RingAdvice privacy policy. Learn how we collect, use and protect your data in compliance with GDPR." lang="en" enPath="/privacy" esPath="/es/privacidad">
<article style="padding:clamp(32px,5vw,64px) 0;">
<div class="container--narrow">
<nav style="margin-bottom:24px;font-size:12px;font-family:monospace;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">
  <a href="/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.35);">ringadvice</a> / <span style="color:#00FFB2;">privacy policy</span>
</nav>
<h1 style="font-size:clamp(24px,4vw,36px);font-weight:400;color:#fff;margin:16px 0 8px;">Privacy Policy</h1>
<p style="font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);font-family:monospace;margin-bottom:32px;">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

<div class="article-content">

<h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
<p>ringadvice.com is operated as an independent editorial project. For privacy-related inquiries, contact us at: <strong>privacy@ringadvice.com</strong></p>

<h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
<p>We collect the following categories of data:</p>
<ul style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);line-height:1.8;">
  <li><strong>Navigation data:</strong> Pages visited, time on site, referring URLs, browser type and operating system. Collected anonymously via analytics tools.</li>
  <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> We use cookies for analytics (Google Analytics) and affiliate tracking. See Section 4 for details.</li>
  <li><strong>No personal data forms:</strong> We do not collect names, emails or addresses unless you contact us directly.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Purpose and Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
<div class="table-wrap">
<table class="comparison-table">
<thead><tr><th>Purpose</th><th>Legal Basis</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Website analytics and performance</td><td>Legitimate interest (Art. 6.1.f GDPR)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Affiliate link tracking</td><td>Consent (Art. 6.1.a GDPR)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Responding to inquiries</td><td>Contract performance (Art. 6.1.b GDPR)</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>

<h2>4. Cookies</h2>
<p>We use the following cookies:</p>
<ul style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);line-height:1.8;">
  <li><strong>_ga, _ga_* (Google Analytics):</strong> Anonymous traffic analytics. Retention: 2 years. You can opt out at <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:#00FFB2;">tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout</a></li>
  <li><strong>Amazon Associates cookies:</strong> Set when you click affiliate links. Allows Amazon to attribute purchases to our referral. Retention: 24 hours (session) or 90 days (cart addition). Governed by Amazon's privacy policy.</li>
</ul>
<p>You can manage or disable cookies through your browser settings at any time.</p>

<h2>5. Your Rights Under GDPR</h2>
<p>As an EU/EEA resident, you have the following rights:</p>
<ul style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);line-height:1.8;">
  <li><strong>Right of access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
  <li><strong>Right of rectification:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
  <li><strong>Right of erasure ("right to be forgotten"):</strong> Request deletion of your data.</li>
  <li><strong>Right to restriction:</strong> Request that we limit the processing of your data.</li>
  <li><strong>Right to data portability:</strong> Receive your data in a machine-readable format.</li>
  <li><strong>Right to object:</strong> Object to processing based on legitimate interests.</li>
  <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent:</strong> Withdraw consent at any time without affecting the lawfulness of prior processing.</li>
</ul>
<p>To exercise any of these rights, email us at <strong>privacy@ringadvice.com</strong>. We will respond within 30 days.</p>

<h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
<p>Analytics data is retained for 26 months. Affiliate tracking data is retained per Amazon's policies (typically 90 days). If you contact us, correspondence is retained for up to 3 years.</p>

<h2>7. International Data Transfers</h2>
<p>Google Analytics may transfer data to the United States. Google LLC participates in the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework. Amazon Associates transfers data per their Privacy Notice, which covers international transfers under Standard Contractual Clauses.</p>

<h2>8. Third-Party Links</h2>
<p>Our site contains links to third-party websites (ouraring.com, samsung.com, ultrahuman.com, amazon.com). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing any personal data.</p>

<h2>9. Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
<p>ringadvice.com participates in the Amazon Associates Program and may participate in other affiliate programs. When you click an affiliate link and make a purchase, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. This does not influence our editorial opinions or recommendations.</p>

<h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision. We encourage you to review this page periodically.</p>

<h2>11. Contact</h2>
<p>For any privacy-related questions or to exercise your rights, contact: <strong>privacy@ringadvice.com</strong></p>

</div>
</div>
</article>
</BaseLayout>
